ry of a Thief)</span><hr size=1> This is from the story of a wild dove...Niema the <br>
rogue.<br>
Upon the stones of gratitude I saw a man half <br>
beaten clinging to the well beside him crying.<br>
What is wrong I thought to myself, somehow my <br>
thoughts slipped into his mind also. He looked up to <br>
me<br>
and met my black eyes, he thought back to me, I <br>
was stoned for thinking to loudly. I blinked away, <br>
how could this be, another has the same gift? The <br>
elders protected her because of her dreams and <br>
Niema knew to well if ever she was captured her <br>
keepers would make her use her great gifts for <br>
evil.<br>
How could it be that this human was not embraced <br>
the same way for his gift but instead stoned?<br>
Yes humans he thought to her, they can not except <br>
the things they feel they can not control.<br>
She shuddered, again not expecting him to hear <br>
her thoughts. <br>
Yet he thought nothing, she could read nothing <br>
from his thoughts.<br>
~is it possible you Human man are so hurt that <br>
you are also afraid I will hurt you if you think to <br>
loudly?~<br>
This time Niema meant to communicate.<br>
He looked up to her eyes swollen and also <br>
blackened, he then emanated a red aura. He invoked fear <br>
into the wild dove an Niema changed form and ran <br>
into the city deep within until she hit a guard <br>
that snapped her right arm when he grabbed her.<br>
&quot;YOU AGAIN!&quot; he shouted loudly into her face.<br>
Niema folded her wings in carefully, and looked <br>
up to him stoically, not thinking or saying a <br>
word.<br>
&quot;Thief I am glad you came to visit us again, <br>
perhaps you are trying to steal, for who this time?&quot;<br>
the militia captain also came to his side <br>
laughing as they formed a cage around the dove.<br>
Niema felt so uncomfortable but did not want to <br>
use her gifts or magic in fear she would meet the <br>
same fate<br>
as the human that feared her near the well.<br>
She blinked and looked up to the captain calmly <br>
stating:<br>
&quot;Milord I am only passing through I wish to catch <br>
the ship at the docks and journey to the land <br>
with mountains to collect flowers for my true <br>
love.&quot;<br>
The captain was unknowingly charmed by the wild <br>
doves black eyes into sympathy,<br>
he command for the guard to unhand her at once. <br>
Then escorted her to the dock and put her on the <br>
ship himself.<br>
She smiled back at him, kindly thanking him for <br>
the escort, <br>
knowing if she had walked alone more of the <br>
merchants and guards would have recognized her.<br>
Niema sat calmly on the bow of the ship, inhaling <br>
the fresh salt air and exhaling the misery she <br>
felt in her mind and soul for the human man.<br>
(end part 1) <br>
